      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DESTROYING (1) goes very well at the course and distance with two wins and a placing from four starts. Scored by 2.5 lengths last time (30.24) in a Grade 4/5 over 530m at this track. Expected to be in the finish. BAREFOOT ZULU (2) has missed the frame at his last couple but placed three back at Wentworth Park and he does perform well here. Has the ability and can find best this time. COMPTON ROCKS (8) lines up chasing another win after getting around the 530m at this track in a handy 30.58 on April 9. Harder here but expected to feature again. MANIFESTO (7) can sneak into the finish again.",
